Raj Kapoor  born Shrishti Nath Kapoor 14 December 1924 â€“ 2 June 1988), also known as Ranbir Raj Kapoor,was an Indian actor, film director and producer, who worked in Hindi cinema.
 Born in Peshawar as the son of Prithviraj Kapoor of the Kapoor family, Raj Kapoor starred in and produced many films for which he received multiple accolades, 
including three National Film Awards and 11 Filmfare Awards in India.
He was inspired by Charlie Chaplin and played characters based on The Tramp in films such as Awaara (1951) and Shree 420 (1955).
